# runc APT Repository

[runc](https://github.com/opencontainers/runc) is a CLI tool for spawning and running containers according to the OCI specification. It is the low-level container runtime used underneath containerd, Docker, Podman, and many other container platforms.

This repository provides **unofficial** Debian/Ubuntu `.deb` packages for runc,
built automatically from official upstream releases and published as an APT repository
at [pkgs.bil.co.ua](https://pkgs.bil.co.ua) via Cloudflare R2.

---

## Compatibility

This package uses the official pre-built upstream binaries from
[opencontainers/runc releases](https://github.com/opencontainers/runc/releases).
The binaries are statically compiled Go executables with no distribution-specific
dependencies, and work on any reasonably modern Debian or Ubuntu release
(`amd64` and `arm64`).

---

## Packages

| Package | Description                                      |
|---------|--------------------------------------------------|
| `runc`  | OCI container runtime binary (`/usr/sbin/runc`)  |

---

## Installation

### 1. Add the GPG signing key

```sh
sudo mkdir -p /etc/apt/keyrings
curl -fsSL {{PAGES_URL}}/public.asc | sudo gpg --dearmor -o /etc/apt/keyrings/runc.gpg
```

### 2. Add the repository

```sh
echo "deb [signed-by=/etc/apt/keyrings/runc.gpg] {{PAGES_URL}} runc main" \
  | sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/runc.list
```

### 3. Pin the repository

```sh
echo -e 'Package: *\nPin: release a=runc\nPin-Priority: 1001' \
  | sudo tee /etc/apt/preferences.d/runc
```

### 4. Update and install

```sh
sudo apt update
sudo apt install runc
```

---

## Package details

### `runc`

- Installs the `runc` binary to `/usr/sbin/`
- No configuration files or systemd units — runc is invoked directly by higher-level runtimes such as containerd
- Runs as **root** — required for namespace and cgroup management

---

## Usage

runc is typically not invoked directly by end users. It is called automatically by container runtimes:

- **containerd** uses `containerd-shim-runc-v2` to delegate container process creation to runc
- **Docker** uses runc as its default OCI runtime via containerd
- **Podman** can use runc as its OCI runtime

To verify the installed version:

```sh
runc --version
```

---

## Build details

- Packages use the official pre-built upstream binaries from [opencontainers/runc releases](https://github.com/opencontainers/runc/releases)
- Packages are GPG-signed
